README

OBJECTIVE:

The objective of this project is to create a Rest API service which will
- Authenticate user with JWT Tokens
- Perform CRUD Operations for a User's list of Favorite books.
- Check for expired token and re-authenticate


*****************************************************************************

INSTRUCTIONS TO GET STARTED:

1 Use 'cd venv' to enter venv directory.
2 Install virtualenv using command- pip install virtualenv.
3 Run command 'pip install -r req.txt' to install all modules in req.txt
4 Finally, venv directory conatins a file called 'favbooks.py'. Run the python file using 'python3 favbooks.py'. Once the program starts running, its now time to test the program.
5 Download Postman or Insomnia to test the Rest API.

***************************************************************************

 INSTRUCTIONS TO TEST THE PROGRAM:

	- To register user:  http://127.0.0.1:5000/register
		Enter 'name' and 'password' in this format- {"name":<name>,"password":<password>}. Change the method to 'POST' and press Send. 
		
		OUTPUT- {
 						 "message": "registered successfully"
						}



	- For user login:  http://127.0.0.1:5000/login
                Click on the Authorization tab and select Basic Authentication. Enter the Username and password registered with. Change method to 'GET' and the press send button to generate a random token. This token is whats required to access favorite books.    
                
		OUTPUT-
						{
  						"token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJwdWJsaWNfaWQiOiI3NDU0YzFhZi02YTE4LTQzYjItYTk1Zi01Njc4NjFjNmYzZTQiLCJleHAiOjE1ODY1OTk2MDF9.2AllM9ZwIxg7sie0lK9JXS6QG6TfnL7TQztZc7vzK0Q"
						}


	-  To see details of all users who have registered:   http://127.0.0.1:5000/users
                Change method to 'GET' and the press send button to generate information of all users.                                    
                
		OUTPUT-                                      
                                                {
 						 "users": [
    							{
      								"name": "Shriya",
      								"password": "sha256$hp1j8NG0$34c2800d7b1b9834d4c839cfd8aa4e8572c0529184111c0463d94a8a200d934d",
      								"public_id": "7454c1af-6a18-43b2-a95f-567861c6f3e4"
    							}
  							]
						}


	-  To add a favorite book:   http://127.0.0.1:5000/addfav
		Enter 'title', 'amazon_url','author','genre' of a favorite book in this format- {"title": <title>,"amazon_url": <amazon_url>,"author": <author_name>,"genre": <genre>}.
		Click on the tab labelled header and enter a new header that looks like 'x-access-tokens' and the value of the header should be the random token generated while logging in.
		Change the method to 'POST' and then press send.
               
                OUTPUT-                                      
						{
 						 "message": "new favourite book added"
						}


	- To see details of all favourite books:   http://127.0.0.1:5000/favbooks
		Click on the tab labelled header and enter a new header that looks like 'x-access-tokens' and the value of the header should be the random token generated while logging in.
                Change method to 'GET' and the press send button to generate information of all favourite books.                                                                            
		                           
                OUTPUT-
						{
 						 "your favorite books": [
    							{
      									"amazon_url": "https://www.amazon.in/Mysterious-Island-Wordsworth-Classics/dp/1840226242/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=mysterious+island&qid=1586598118&sr=8-1",
      									"author": "Jules Verne",
      									"genre": "Mystery",
      									"id": 1,
      									"title": "The Mysterious island"
    							}
  							]
						}


	- To delete a favourite book: http://127.0.0.1:5000/favbooks/<book_id>
		Click on the tab labelled header and enter a new header that looks like 'x-access-tokens' and the value of the header should be the random token generated while logging in.
                Change method to 'DELETE' and the press send button.
                                                                            
		OUTPUT-                                      
						{
 						 "message": "Book deleted"
						}


	- To update a favourite book:   http://127.0.0.1:5000/favbooks/<book_id>
		Click on the tab labelled header and enter a new header that looks like 'x-access-tokens' and the value of the header should be the random token generated while logging in.
		Change method the 'PUT' and press the send button to update the book with book_id.
		
		OUTPUT- 
						{
 						 "message": "Book updated"
						} 

